UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 66/GA
1 AN ACT relating to public agencies.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS 61.870 TO 61.884 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) A public agency with a board or commission of appointed or elected members
6 shall publish information on its appointed and elected members on its website for
7 the duration of each member's term, including:
8 (a) The name of each member;
9 (b) Each member's date of appointment or election;
10 (c) The date that the term of each member ends; and
11 (d) An official method to contact each member.
12 (2) If a public agency does not have a website, it shall have the information described
13 in subsection (1)(a) to (d) of this section published by a related public agency on
14 its website.
15 Section 2. KRS 61.826 is amended to read as follows:
16 (1) A public agency may conduct any meeting entirely through publicly available
17 video teleconference to carry out its public business, including but not limited to:
18 (a) Advisory actions;
19 (b) Informational meetings;
20 (c) Rendering decisions on individual cases before the public agency subject to
21 the limitations of KRS 61.810; and
22 (d) Approving business transactions of a routine nature.
23 (2) A public agency shall convene, at a minimum, a quorum of members in person,
24 and allow other members to attend, participate, and vote through video
25 teleconference in accordance with KRS 61.805 to 61.850 for any of the following
26 actions:
27 (a) Final actions establishing or modifying laws or regulations;
Page 1 of 3
