UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 66/GA
1 (b) Final actions establishing or modifying taxes;
2 (c) Approving or denying a nonroutine expenditure; and
3 (d) Approving or denying an award or grant of public funds in excess of one
4 hundred thousand dollars ($100,000).
5 (3) A public agency shall be exempt from the requirements of subsection (2) of this
6 section during a declared state of emergency.
7 (4) A public agency may develop policies and procedures to allow members to
8 participate in a meeting using video teleconference, including but not be limited
9 to:
10 (a) Attendance and participation policies for members of the public agency that
11 attend virtually through video teleconference. The policies shall at
12 minimum require the members to:
13 1. Be considered present and in attendance at the meeting;
14 2. Be permitted to vote; and
15 3. Remain visible through his or her camera on the electronic device
16 connected to the video teleconference meeting;
17 (b) Governing the request, notification, and decision framework process for
18 members to attend virtually through video teleconference for meetings
19 subject to the requirements of this section;
20 (c) Accommodation of requests received from a member due to:
21 1. A temporary or permanent disability or other medical condition of the
22 member that prevents in-person attendance; and
23 2. A personal matter that impedes the ability of the member to participate
24 in person, including but not limited to personal or family emergencies,
25 severe weather conditions, and transportation issues; and
26 (d) Ensuring that all records and recordings of video teleconference meetings
27 comply with the Open Records Act, KRS 61.870 to 61.884.
