1 (5)[(2)] Notice of a video teleconference meeting shall:
2 (a) Comply with the requirements of KRS 61.820 or 61.823 as appropriate;
3 (b) Clearly state that the meeting will be a video teleconference;
4 (c) Provide specific information on how any member of the public or media
5 organization may view the meeting electronically; and
6 (d) In any case where the public agency is providing[ has elected to provide] a
7 physical location, in accordance with subsection (2) of this section, or in any
8 circumstance where two (2) or more members of the public agency are
9 attending a video teleconference meeting from the same physical location,
10 precisely identify a primary physical location of the video teleconference
11 where all members can be seen and heard and the public may attend in
12 accordance with KRS 61.840.
13 (6)[(3)] The same procedures with regard to participation, distribution of materials,
14 and other matters shall apply in all video teleconference locations. Members of the
15 public agency who participate in a video teleconference shall remain visible on
16 camera at all times that business is being discussed.
17 (7)[(4)] Any interruption in the video or audio broadcast of a video teleconference at
18 any location shall result in the suspension of the video teleconference until the
19 broadcast is restored.
20 (8)[(5)] If a regular meeting is changed to a video conference, the meeting shall
21 remain a regular meeting if the meeting occurs on the same date and time as
22 originally scheduled and the public agency follows the provisions of KRS 61.823(4)
23 to provide a notice that meets the requirements of subsection (5)[(2)](b) to (d) of
24 this section.
